    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-19T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-19T02:00:00-05:00" n="611"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4327: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-19T16:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 16, 6 p.m. I think the policy is not only adequate and feasible but is
                    also one which will avoid involving us in a civil war in Siberia. The success of
                    such a policy will depend on the measure of support which it receives from the
                    other interested governments. The present conflict of policy is creating a
                    dangerous situation.</p>
                <p>I will not discuss the subject with the authorities here until I receive further
                    instructions from you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
